@startuml
autonumber
skinparam BoxPadding 10
skinparam ParticipantPadding 10

actor "Client (Company Manager)" as Client
box "Frontend (Flutter App)" #LightBlue
  participant "LeaveScreen" as LeaveUI
  participant "Supabase Client SDK" as SDK
end box

box "Backend (Supabase & PostgreSQL)" #LightGreen
  participant "PostgreSQL Database" as DB
  participant "Realtime Service" as RT
end box

actor "Manager (HMI Stars)" as HMI

== Step 1: Submit Leave Request ==
Client -> LeaveUI : Fill & submit leave form
LeaveUI -> SDK : insert() leave request details
SDK -> DB : Insert row in 'conges' table
note over DB : PostgreSQL RLS verifies company_id matching user session
DB --> SDK : Row created successfully
SDK --> LeaveUI : Display success status

== Step 2: Real-time Notification ==
DB -> RT : Trigger CDC (Change Data Capture)
RT -> HMI : Push real-time notification / dashboard update
note over HMI : HMI Manager is notified of the new request (read-only)

== Step 3: Process Leave Request ==
Client -> LeaveUI : Review request & click "Approve" / "Reject"
LeaveUI -> SDK : update() leave request status
SDK -> DB : Update status in 'conges' table
DB --> SDK : Status updated successfully
SDK --> LeaveUI : Refresh UI showing new status
DB -> RT : Trigger CDC on update
RT -> HMI : Push real-time update to HMI dashboard

@enduml
